






#lg A	kirugu


@(A.1 = 1-8) He has abandoned his cow-pen and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold. The wild bull has abandoned his cow-pen and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold. The lord of all the lands has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold. @wDN{Enlil} has abandoned the shrine @wSN{Nibru} and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold. His wife @wDN{Ninlil} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. @wDN{Ninlil} has abandoned that house, the @wTN{Ki-ur}, and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. The queen of @wSN{Keš} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. @wDN{Ninmaḫ} has abandoned that house @wSN{Keš} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold.

@(A.9 = 9-18) She of @wSN{Isin} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. @wDN{Ninisina} has abandoned the shrine @wTN{Egal-maḫ} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. The queen of @wSN{Unug} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. @wDN{Inana} has abandoned that house @wSN{Unug} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. @wDN{Nanna} has abandoned @wSN{Urim} and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold. @wDN{Suen} has abandoned @wTN{E-kiš-nu-ŋal} and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold. His wife @wDN{Ningal} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. @wDN{Ningal} has abandoned her @wTN{Agrun-kug} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. The wild bull of @wSN{Eridug} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold. @wDN{Enki} has abandoned that house @wSN{Eridug} and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold.

@(A.18A = 18A-26) 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds 1 line:} …… @noteref{partially preserved name of a goddess} has abandoned that house @wSN{Larag} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold.
}  @wDN{Šara} has abandoned @wTN{E-maḫ} and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold. @wDN{Ud-saḫara} has abandoned that house @wSN{Umma} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. @wDN{Bau} has abandoned @wSN{Iri-kug} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. She has abandoned her flooded chamber and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. Her son @wDN{Ab-Bau} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold. @wDN{Ab-Bau} has abandoned @wTN{Ma-gu-ena} and has let the breezes haunt his sheepfold. The protective goddess of the holy house has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold.

@(A.26 = 26-34) The protective goddess has abandoned @wTN{E-tar-sirsir} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. The mother of @wSN{Lagaš} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. @wDN{Ŋatumdug} has abandoned that house @wSN{Lagaš} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. She of @wSN{Niŋin} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. The great queen has abandoned that house @wSN{Sirara} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. She of @wSN{Kinirša} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. @wDN{Dumuzid-abzu} has abandoned that house @wSN{Kinirša} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. She of @wSN{Gu-aba} has abandoned it and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold. @wDN{Ninmarki} has abandoned the shrine @wSN{Gu-aba} and has let the breezes haunt her sheepfold.

